      <akn:section eId="sec_7_651_04">
        <akn:num>7-651.04</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Comfort care bracelet or necklace.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-651_04_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>EMS personnel shall recognize only a comfort care bracelet or necklace for purposes of withholding cardiopulmonary resuscitation or advanced life support.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-651_04_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor shall approve the design for a comfort care bracelet and necklace. The bracelet and necklace shall be easily identifiable and designed so that the following information is visible:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-651_04_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The comfort care bracelet and necklace shall be metal, except that the Mayor may issue a plastic temporary bracelet and necklace for use by a patient until the metal bracelet or necklace is received.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
